					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The graphics are only 2 bit color depth, so small size is no surprise (that rhymed... Unintentionally...).
<br />
<br />But you are right about one thing; all the graphics can't possibly be there. First of all, it's labled as a .NES file, but it's not a NES file, it's a graphics file. Open it with YY-CHR or some Tile Editor to view the graphics. I don't see Megaman's graphics there, or really any enemies. I see Dr. Wily on the top, and then the words "Mega Man" below that. There's some level tile data, but no sprites I don't think. Also, there are big dark spaces between the level graphics.
<br />
<br />Also, you should probably know what you're doing a little more before you attempt to remake MM9 on the NES. This is kind of a big project... You should learn 6502 and whatnot.</div>

